  "title": "Construction Design Manager #79141",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Construction</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Construction Design Manager</strong></li><li>Working Location: Ang Mo Kio</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon – Fri, 9.30am – 6.30pm; Sat, 9.30am – 12.30pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $5,000 + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage the full project lifecycle—planning schedules, implementing work, and overseeing site operations—from concept through completion, including TOP (Temporary Occupation Permit) and DLP (Defects Liability Period) stages.</li><li>Read and produce architectural, structural, and mechanical & electrical (M&E) drawings.</li><li>Set and manage timelines, budgets, and quality standards.</li><li>Develop creative exterior and interior layouts for residential projects.</li><li>Coordinate with key stakeholders and conduct regular site visits to report on progress.</li><li>Perform other duties as assigned.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Architecture, Civil or Structural Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>At least 3 years of relevant project design and management experience in Singapore; equivalent experience will be considered.</li><li>Able to manage projects independently.</li><li>Self-motivated, results-oriented team player who can also work independently.</li><li>Strong interpersonal and people-management skills.</li><li>Proficient with design software (e.g., ArchiCAD, Lumion) and presentation tools (e.g., Photoshop, SketchUp, PowerPoint).</li><li>Able to work on Saturdays when required.</li><li>Comfortable working in a fast-paced environment.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79141 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
